majordomo (0.1.5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add `majordomo send`: post a message to a space, or reply in a thread,
    through the CLI and the MCP server. The privacy sieve refuses blocked
    spaces; a set WORLD_AS_OF refuses every send; `login` now also mints
    the message-create scope (re-run it once before the first send).
  * Rename the direct-API surface to `api`: the pip extra becomes
    `majordomo[api]` and the optional config table `[api]`. The
    `--nocache` read flag keeps its name.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:21:25 +1000

majordomo (0.1.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add `--live` (cache plus active-space top-up) and rename the API-bypass
    path to `--nocache`.
  * Publish to PyPI (`pip install majordomo`); the Homebrew formula now tracks
    the PyPI sdist.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Tue, 30 Jun 2026 22:31:35 +1000

majordomo (0.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security: stop Typer dumping locals on crash (the live-login traceback
    exposed the OAuth client secret and authorization code); guard the login
    flow with a clean error.

